# General code standards

- Prefer small, focused changes.
- Preserve existing architecture and naming patterns.
- Match the style of nearby code.
- Avoid speculative abstractions.
- Avoid large refactors unless explicitly requested.
- Keep functions short and single-purpose when practical.
- Prefer clear names over clever names.
- Do not introduce new dependencies without explaining why.
- Do not leave TODOs unless the issue explicitly asks for follow-up work.
- No dead code, commented-out code, debug prints, or unrelated formatting churn.
